Description: Venus is the second closest planet to the Sun and the hottest with temperatures as high as 740K and as low as 300K. Venus has an acidic atmosphere approximately 65 km thick. Being about the same size as Earth, Venus is considered Earth's evil twin. Venus is so violent, a slight breeze would feel like being hit by an ocean wave on Earth.
